About Me

I'm Kanjanaroj Khamkhom,Computer Engineering (Year 4) Passionate about technology and innovation

I am currently a 4th year undergraduate student in Computer Engineering. With my interest in technology since I was a child, I started by disassembling and assembling computers by myself, and was encouraged by my family to continuously study and experiment with new things. This passion led me to study Computer Engineering to develop knowledge and skills that can be applied to future technologies.

MY WORK

My Work : Nonstop Learning in the Tech World

Whether my work comes from classroom projects or self-study, it is important for my future academic and career path. Studying computer engineering has no fixed boundaries because technology is constantly changing. Starting a project now is preparing me to adapt and develop myself along with the changes in the digital

Starting a project today is not just about completing a task-it is about preparing myself to adapt, solve problems, and grow alongside the rapid changes in the digital world. By constantly improving my skills and experimenting with new technologies, I can ensure that I am ready for any future challenge. I can ensure that I am ready for any challenge the future holds. My journey in technology is not just about acquiring knowledge; it is about applying it in meaningful ways to create impactful solutions.

ACTIVITY

Participating in university activities : the first step to real learning

I have a motto for my university life and I have participated in both formal and informal activities. These activities are equally important because they help me develop a variety of skills. They are also an opportunity to network, build relationships with seniors and juniors, and learn how to adapt to a wider society.

Participating in university activities is not just about having fun, but also about understanding ourselves and others better, and preparing us to cope with the future world of work and society. These experiences shape our growth and equip us with the confidence needed to face future challenges.
